001package com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.response.historyLog;
002
003import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;
004import com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.annotations.HistoryLogProps;
005import com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.helpers.Bytes;
006
007import java.math.BigInteger;
008
009/**
010 * NOTE: not used in current firmware
011 */
012@HistoryLogProps(
013    opCode = 151,
014    displayName = "CGM Data Sample",
015    usedByTidepool = true
016)
017public class CgmDataSampleHistoryLog extends HistoryLog {
018    
019    private int status;
020    private int value;
021    
022    public CgmDataSampleHistoryLog() {}
023    public CgmDataSampleHistoryLog(long pumpTimeSec, long sequenceNum, int status, int value) {
024        super(pumpTimeSec, sequenceNum);
025        this.cargo = buildCargo(pumpTimeSec, sequenceNum, status, value);
026        this.status = status;
027        this.value = value;
028        
029    }
030
031    public CgmDataSampleHistoryLog(int status, int value) {
032        this(0, 0, status, value);
033    }
034
035    public int typeId() {
036        return 151;
037    }
038
039    /**
040     * <table border="1">
041     * <caption>Parsed fields for CgmDataSampleHistoryLog:</caption>
042     * <tr><td><code>status</code></td><td><code>Bytes.readShort(raw, 10)</code></td></tr>
043     * <tr><td><code>value</code></td><td><code>Bytes.readShort(raw, 19)</code></td></tr>
044     * </table>
045     */
046    public void parse(byte[] raw) {
047        Validate.isTrue(raw.length == 26);
048        this.cargo = raw;
049        parseBase(raw);
050        this.status = Bytes.readShort(raw, 10);
051        this.value = Bytes.readShort(raw, 19);
052        
053    }
054
055    public static byte[] buildCargo(long pumpTimeSec, long sequenceNum, int status, int value) {
056        return HistoryLog.fillCargo(Bytes.combine(
057            new byte[]{-105, 0}, // (byte) 151
058            Bytes.toUint32(pumpTimeSec),
059            Bytes.toUint32(sequenceNum),
060            Bytes.firstTwoBytesLittleEndian(status), 
061            Bytes.firstTwoBytesLittleEndian(value)));
062    }
063    public int getStatus() {
064        return status;
065    }
066    public int getValue() {
067        return value;
068    }
069    
070}
